test-rating.description: GreatSchools Ratings for Vermont are based on the 2012-2013 New England Common Assessment Program (NECAP) reading, writing, math, and science results. GreatSchools compared the test results for all elementary and middle school grades and compared them to the test results for all Vermont elementary and middle schools. Grade 11 results were compared to the test results for all Vermont high schools. Please note, private schools are not required to release test results, so ratings are available only for public schools. GreatSchools Ratings cannot be compared across states, because of differences in the states' standardized testing programs. Keep in mind that when comparing schools using GreatSchools Ratings it's important to factor in other information, including the quality of each school's teachers, the school culture, special programs, etc.
